Section 1:
Act 135 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H2/4/25 H2/5/25 H2/10/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1189
4
5 By: Representative Vaught
6 By: Senator G. Leding
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND NOVICE TEACHER MENTORING REQUIREMENTS
10 UNDER THE TEACHER EXCELLENCE AND SUPPORT SYSTEM; AND
11 FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
12
13
Subtitle
14
15 AN ACT TO AMEND NOVICE TEACHER MENTORING
16 REQUIREMENTS UNDER THE TEACHER
17 EXCELLENCE AND SUPPORT SYSTEM; AND FOR
18 OTHER PURPOSES.
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
21
22 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 6-17-2806(d), concerning the requirement
23 for novice teacher mentoring under the Teacher Excellence and Support System,
24 is amended to read as follows:
25 (d)(1) The Teacher Excellence and Support System also shall include
26 novice teacher mentoring for each novice teacher employed at the public
27 school that:
28 (1)(A) Provides training and support to novice teachers to
29 increase teacher retention;
30 (2)(B) Establishes norms of professionalism; and
31 (3)(C) Leads to improved student achievement by increasing
32 effective teacher performance.
33 (2) However, a novice teacher who has completed a Division of
34 Elementary and Secondary Education-approved year-long residency is not
35 required to participate in novice teacher mentoring under this subsection
36 (d).
